  "title": "STR-Bamba: Multimodal Molecular Textual Representation Encoder-Decoder Foundation Model",
  "experiments_summary": "The paper presents STR-Bamba426M, a 426M-parameter hybrid encoder-decoder model combining Transformer and Mamba-2 layers. A custom Byte-Pair Encoding (BPE) tokenizer was developed with pre-tokenization for seven molecular representations (SMILES, SELFIES, InChI, IUPAC name, molecular formula, SPG for polymers, and electrolyte formulations), resulting in a 5000-token vocabulary. The model was pre-trained in two phases on 588M samples (~29B tokens) from 117M PubChem molecules, 2M polymers, and 258 electrolyte formulations using 396 A100 GPUs for phase 1 (encoder training with masked language modeling and sentence embedding for representation alignment) and 8 A100 GPUs for phase 2 (decoder training for molecular reconstruction). The architecture features 24 layers (1024 hidden dimensions) with attention layers at positions 6 and 18, Mamba-2 layers elsewhere, cross-attention for encoder-decoder connection, Grouped Query Attention, and Rotary Position Embeddings. Experiments included: (1) latent space analysis using t-SNE visualization and K-means clustering (n=2-10) on 2000 samples per modality, evaluated with Davies-Bouldin Index, Adjusted Rand Index, V-Measure, and Fowlkes-Mallows Score; (2) property prediction on 99 tasks across 29 datasets (MoleculeNet benchmark for small molecules, 17 polymer datasets, 2 electrolyte datasets) using both pre-trained models with XGBoost and fine-tuned models with 2-layer fully connected networks, with hyperparameter optimization via Tree-Structured Parzen Estimator (TPE) to identify top-3 representation combinations, all with 5 different seeds; (3) molecular representation translation evaluated on 3007 random molecules using validity, structural similarity (Tanimoto), BLEU-1, BLEU-2, and Jaccard similarity metrics."
